<s docid="FBIS3-43040" num="193"> In the subsector, wastes from the sawmilling industry are used for manufacturing particle board and mail (postal) boxes, constructing temporary structures in the sector's own ancillary facilities, and selling to state farms and collective farms (sawdust) and the public (trim, slabs, and lumber that has already been used).</s>

