<s docid="FT934-9592" num="4"> FT 10 NOV 93 / Tyre power</s>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<s docid="FT934-9592" num="5"> THE first UK plant to produce electricity from waste tyres formally opened in Wolverhampton yesterday.</s>

<s docid="FT934-9592" num="6"> The plant expects to recycle 10m tyres a year, 21 per cent of the total discarded in the UK.</s>

<s docid="FT934-9592" num="7"> It is owned by Elm Energy & Recycling, a subsidiary of Nipsco, the US electrical utility.</s>
