<s docid="FBIS3-24648" num="280"> Much of the current Japanese effort to promote the development and sale of low-pollution automobiles focuses on natural gas vehicles, which use methane-based city gas, and which are categorized according to method of fuel storage: compressed natural gas vehicles (CNGVs), liquefied natural gas vehicles (LNGVs), and absorption natural gas vehicles (ANGVs).</s>

<s docid="FBIS3-24648" num="281"> As of November 1993, there were 123 natural gas vehicles (NGVs) in use in Japan, mostly owned by city gas companies; eighteen of them are leased to local governments under the auspices of the Ministry of Transport.</s>

