<s docid="FBIS3-24648" num="323"> EUROPE: CAUTIOUS APPROACH TO LOW-POLLUTION VEHICLES Tougher clean-air standards to be implemented in both California and Europe by the year 2000 will dictate the sale of zero-emission and ultralow-emission vehicles.</s>

<s docid="FBIS3-24648" num="324"> European automakers are taking a cautious approach in preparing for the new standards.</s>

<s docid="FBIS3-24648" num="325"> In many cases this means converting conventional models to electric drive; in other cases it means designing scaled-down models with smaller, less polluting internal combustion engines.</s>

<s docid="FBIS3-24648" num="326"> The most advanced designs, now on the drawing boards, will not be marketed before the year 2000.</s>

